-# Audit-history section for Work / Collection / Community show pages.
-#
-# Locals:
-#   resource_id — the Atlas resource ID to fetch history for
-#
-# Gated by `can?(:read, :audit_event)` so that broadening the audience
-# (piece 5 — acting-as) becomes a one-line Ability change rather than a
-# view hunt. Per-event rendering dispatches to `_event_<action>` partials
-# with `_event_generic` as the fallback — adding a new action type is a
-# new file, not a case-statement edit.
-#
-# Performance trade-off (v1 admin-only, acceptable): fires an inline HTTP
-# request to Atlas every show-page render. Piece 5 broadening the audience
-# may motivate moving to a Turbo Frame so history loads asynchronously.
- if can?(:read, :audit_event)
  - history = AtlasRb::Resource.history(resource_id, nuid: Current.nuid)
  - events = Array(history['events'])
  %section.audit-history.mt-4
    %h3 History
    - if events.empty?
      %p.text-muted No recorded events.
    - else
      %ol.audit-event-list.list-unstyled{reversed: true}
        - events.each do |event|
          = render partial: "audit_events/event_#{event['action']}",
                   locals: { event: event },
                   default: 'audit_events/event_generic'
